# Euclid's algorithm: gcd(48, 36) = 12, proven at compile time. The loop
# `while b != 0: t = a % b; a = b; b = t` runs over concrete values, so the
# closing `require` is only reachable-as-satisfied if the result is right.
# Boots under qemu-riscv64 and exits 0.
#
# Registers: a0 = a, a1 = b, t0 = a % b.
a0 = 48
a1 = 36
while a1 != 0:
    t0 = a0 % a1
    a0 = a1
    a1 = t0
t3 = 12
require a0 == t3
exit(0)
